out_fmt:
Strict JSON format:
{
    "original_question": "original question",
    "sub_questions": ["sub-question 1", ...],
    "combination": {
        "type": "parallel|serial|compare|aggregate",
        "description": "combination method description",
        "dependencies": []
    }
}
Note: The combination field explains how sub-questions are combined. type options: parallel (parallel independent), serial (serial dependency), compare (comparison type), aggregate (aggregation statistics). dependencies is a dependency index array (only valid for serial, e.g., [0] means depends on the result of the 1st sub-question).
